headline.main: Two Japanese Destroyers Struck, Transport Sunk Off New Ireland

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN THE SOUTHWEST PACIFIC, Friday, Dec. 3 -- Attacking increased Japanese shipping off New Ireland, United States planes scored direct hits on two destroyers, set a large tanker aflame and sank a big transport.
abstract: US planes hit 2 destroyers, fire tanker and sink transport, New Ireland area; bomb Borgen Bay, New Brit; fire air strip and down 10 Jap planes, Wewak
